A new era of crisis begins. 
France and the rest of Europe are in the sights of investors. 
A statistical tornado rose Tuesday on Europe. 
Each state has published the information reltives to GDP for the 3A. 
The Czech economy has stagnated this last quarter, while France and Germany are growing. 
The bond market is breaking all records. 
Investors are watching not only Italy, but also Spain, France, Austria and others. 
The statistical offices of the eurozone, Germany, Czech Republic and other European countries have issued earlier visions of economic development for the third quarter. 
The GDP of Germany has forecast growth of 0.5%, France 0.4%. 
Both countries have changed the data for the second quarter during which Germany is better placed than expected (growth of 0.3% instead of the expected 0.1%), but France has reported a slight decline of 0.1% (it was at the root of stagnation). 
The Czech economy has had a growth rate of 1.5% in the third quarter. 
But GDP has stagnated, according to the Office of the Czech statistical office confirmed that it is heading towards a gradual reduction in economic growth. 
The results are worse than the forecast of analysts. 
The most important events: 
The Czech économiqe has had a growth rate of 1.5% during the third quarter but has stagnated for last quarter. 
The German economy has been in the third quarter growth of 0, 5% according to the data provided and recalculated periodically. 
The economy of the eurozone and the European Union has had a growth rate of 0.2% between July and September compared to the previous quarter, which corresponds to what had planned analysts. 
The Greek economy has fallen by 5.2%. 
The yield on the 10-year bonds is 28,45% 
The bond yields of Spain and Italy are starting to rise to critical limits. 
The problems begin to feel in Austria, France, Belgium, etc... 
The Czech bond yields are maintienent below 4% while the situation is deteriorating in the region. 
Voices in Germany to say that the ECB should be the guarantee of last resort. 
