Iranian students are ready to die for the nuclear program of their country. 
They have created a human shield 
A few hundred students from graduate schools have created a human shield around a nuclear site in Iran. 
They want to support the nuclear program of their country by this gesture in response to a possible Israeli attack. 
Students have begun to pray at noon at the site and then wished the death of the US and Israel. 
A few hundred students from the universities of Isfahan have created a human shield around the nuclear technology center in Esfahan is processed uranium. 
They have openly stated that they would defend the nuclaire of their country at the risk of their own lives. 
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) noted in its latest information that Iran has not ceased to strengthen its nuclear weapons. 
Reports in Israel of a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities. 
Students have begun to pray at noon at the site and then wished the death of the US and Israel. 
