The diet of an obese child: do not take breakfast and takes the deli for lunch 
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 years were overweight, 9% of écoliersont weight above average and 5% are obese. 
As shown by the current research obese children come from families who have an unhealthy lifestyle. 
This shows once again how important is the environment in which humans and models that surround it. 
On the tables of obese children is an example of the deli 50% more often than in families of children with normal weight. 
19% of obese had dinner fries, according to the survey conducted with an awareness "obesity is not an accident." 
In the families of small big sport is not also a habit, which is now the case of most of today's schoolchildren - only 15% replied that at least once a week parents found time for active movement. 
Investigation of 900 children 
The survey was conducted during the last school year and 900 students of primary schools in Czech Republic. 
It was the second edition of "the Obesity is no coincidence," supported by the General Insurance and Unilever. 
 Since the beginning is more than 12,000 students from sixth to third who have enrolled in the project. 
One of the key factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of children who are overweight or obese, is the lack of a proper diet and not enough physical exercise. 
"Only half the children interviewed said for example eat five times a day, breakfast, lunch, dinner, which is one of the basic principles of good nutrition," said one of the results of the investigation. 
Without breakfast and dinner Deli 
Experts draw attention to the fact that a healthy development requires a few basic details such as a breakfast at the same time. 
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of the families of students eat at the same time. 
In the majority of families each takes his breakfast alone. 
And the worst that has been raised is that a tenth of the population does not breakfast. 
Breakfast is the basis of a good daily diet. 
The survey showed that in families of obese children often consume unhealthy fries. 
Almost every pupil - not to mention the weight - drink every day drinks sweet (70%). 
More than 40% of children interviewed sport regularly, but for parents it is half, only 15%. 
Prepares you your diet 
Another part of the investigation has allowed selected children (204 boys and girls of 13 schools) to prepare their own food options according to their own taste and their personal opinion. 
"The preferences of Czech children from 12 to 15 years away, a healthy diet, the ideal." 
Among their favourite dishes, there is a lot of cakes, meat and sweets. 
"The most alarming is a large preference for sweet lemonades," is indicated in the results of the investigation. 
For lunch the pasta that took the first place just before the white meat. 
Children are not at all wanted starch and preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low. 
Focus on health 
The investigation has shown that children are ready to change their habits when they receive the relevant information. 
"During a review of a group of participants in the survey who had completed the questionnaire after the outreach session" obesity is not an accident ," it was assité with a definite willingness to move towards a healthy diet," indicate the results of the investigation. 
The most marked example in relation to sweet lemonades because children have begun to give preference to water consumption. 
Children are most often checked on the questionnaire white meat and fish as a main dish and cut the sweet dishes and "knedliky" (spécialté Czech dumplings meal of bread or potatoes). 
