The company of the railways has developed a plan - crisis, which aims to prevent train accidents in winter. 
The number of employees is expected to double. 
It costs millions. 
In the fight against the train accidents related to the winter season and delays, the railway "Deutsche Bahn" will spend more than 70 million more this year. 
The daily Bild Zeitung reported earlier, citing an internal crisis in the group, that investments of a total of about 300 million euros would be provided until 2015. 
This should allow greater availability of vehicles and the rail network in the event of extreme weather conditions. 
The number of internal and external employees for snow removal of rail facilities and docks is expected to double between 16,000 people. 
The aim is to rid the docks of snow and ice until the beginning of the phase of service and 90% of the equipment needed to service within a period of four to five hours. 
There are two months ago the Chief of Station Rüdiger Grube warned the government and industry at a conference at the top of the train accidents this winter. 
Last winter the railways had a lot of problems for transport users, because it lacks reserves in case of difficult weather conditions. 
So many new regional trains have been waiting for permission from the Ministry of Railways. 
In addition, there is a delay in the delivery of trains. 
The railway company has for years what to do, given that it needs to check the axles of trains ICE much more often in the workshop, after a break of axles took place on ICE in the central railway station in Cologne. 
