These documents have lost considerable value during the financial crisis and have led banks to the bottom. 
"We are pleased to be able to find a solution to this issue, without the parties initiate a procedure in court," said a spokesman of the Deutsche Bank in New York. 
The Bank has acknowledged no fault comparison. 
This applies also to Citigroup, which has committed itself to a payment of an amount of $20.5 million. 
