The National Credit Union Administration (NCUA) responsible for cooperative banks in the United States and it intervenes in the event of bankruptcy, in order to protect the deposits of customers. 
The NCUA is trying to repair the damage of several billion dollars. 
Comparisons now are the first of their kind. 
The regulator has also taken other major banks and he summoned before the Court JP Morgan Chase, the Royal Bank of Scotland and Goldman Sachs. 
With regard to the issue of mortgage documents "Mortgage Securities." 
Credit institutions are at the base. 
When the housing bubble US erupted in 2007, it was fatal for a large number of banking companies. 
In September 2008, at the peak of the financial crisis, the investment bank Lehman Brothers collapsed. 
Even if the events are already a few years ago, at the moment it is blowing on the US banks a wind storm. 
Investors and supervisory authorities have filed numerous appeals to obtain compensation or to punish breaches. 
The Federal Housing Finance Agency (FHFA) has triggered the biggest wave of complaints. 
It accuses 18 major international banks, two financial house US Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac " benefit in kind in mortgages of about 200 billion dollars. 
Deutsche Bank must also file an appeal with the FHFA, several operations of a total of $14.2 billion for the years 2005 to 2007. 
The supervisory authorities are demanding that the Frankfurter addresses "substantial losses" but without mentioning a specific sum. 
Deutsche Bank had rejected the applications as unjustified and says it wants to defend itself. 
