Equally incredible is that Boeing has received this order: the Middle East, a growing gold mine of future orders for aircraft. 
In forecasts published Monday, the Chicago company believes that the airlines of the Middle East will need in the next 20 years of 2,520 planes for a total value of $450 billion. 
Over the weekend, Boeing was informed of the order of commercial aircraft the most expensive of its history - 50 Boeing 777 corridors. 
It is the airline Emirates based in Dubai that has spent this gargantuan order. 
