Adversity has slowed the economy 
During the first year of Mario López Valdez, Sinaloa unemployment and informality have increased, foreign investment has fallen and the economy shrank 
2011 is a year that will be remembered in the economic history of Sinaloa, it is the first year of Government of Mario López Valdez, called the change, which has generated great expectations with regard to the advances of the economy, but given the climate adversity from the beginning of the year, the increase is not observed, there is a deterioration of the main indicators of economic development. 
Temperatures in February, causing losses of trillions for the agricultural sector, have limited the possibilities of the economy of the state for growth, have caused a contraction of economic activity in general by 3.6% in the first half of the year, mainly justified by the historical decline of 31,16% in agriculture, which has affected the dynamism of other economic sectors. 
According to the report by the frozen allocations from the Mexican Council of Rural Development Soutenable, there has been damage of 582 million 835 hectares, including a 78.03 percent have suffered total damage and the rest of 21,07% have suffered partial damage, the main crops affected were vegetables, corn and chickpeas. 
The decline in economic activity has generated, until November, a steady rise in unemployment in the state, according to the National Institute of Statistics and Geography the unemployment rate in the state during the first three quarters of the year there has been a rapid increase, because while the January to March, 55,000,053 sinaloens were unemployed, with a rate of 4.53% of Population Economics Active, in the second quarter the rate became 5.28% and from July to September, the average has continued to raise up to $6.19 percent, a rate that represents more than 74 sinaloens thousand unemployed, an increase compared to the first half of 18 thousand people 969. 
Less liquidity 
Unemployment in Sinaloa during the year is multifactorial, according to the economist Gerardo Lopez Cervantes, director of the Faculty of Social and Economic Sciences of the UAS, rising unemployment can be explained indirectly depending on the actions carried out by public policy. 
"What we see is a rise in unemployment, which is due to various factors, among which the loss of liquidity in the market due to a restriction of resources by the legislation approved in the Congress to combat the laundering of money, because for people who earn dollars illegally is not easy as they work to earn, invest and use them in something," he said. 
Migration 
López Cervantes pointed out that the rise in unemployment is also due to a demographic factor. 
"The number of people who leave the state to go to work abroad, the United States has been restricted, first because of the difficulties of entry and secondly because they already have a lot of difficulties in finding work, these people remain here and ask for sources of work, which means that unemployment rise," said. 
Lack of seriousness 
The analysis of the sinaloen labour market worsens in considering the high level of lack of seriousness that predominates among the working conditions, according to the INEGI, 60,38% of the population in this state are working without pay as a worker with no social insurance institution. 
Unemployment and the lack of seriousness, another reason for the discrepancy is the low wages, the entity has the lowest salaries, according to the records of the Mexican Institute of Social Insurance and the Secretariat of Labour and Social Welfare. 
The average monthly income of sinaloens workers was, until September, 5,000,352 pesos, well below the national average, which stands at 7 thousand 375 pesos. 
Contraction of FDI 
The decline in economic activity and rising unemployment, 2011 saw the greatest reduction of Foreign Direct Investment in the last 10 years, according to the Secretariat for Economic Affairs from January to June the state's FDI reached 630,000,697, which represents a decrease of 87.74% compared to the 5,143,000 312 million recorded in the same period of the previous year. 
In turn, the Secretariat of Economic Development of the Government of the State recorded a total investment of 17,280 trillion pesos per year, mainly by service sector companies. 
Debt 
Given the scenario of economic contraction, the Government of the state has requested in July at the congress public approval of a credit of 3 trillion pesos, earmarked for investment in infrastructure projects in the 18 municipes, with the aim to reactivate the economy, the approval of the Congress of the State has been to 2,600 trillion pesos and until November there has been no benefit of debt in any sector of the economy of the state. 
Reactions 
For the representatives of the business sector, the first year of Government of Mario López Valdés demonstrates a lack of management capacity of the Government. 
Miguel López Loredo, president of the National Industry Chamber of Transformation, said that in 2011 there has been no harmonisation of the wishes of the different sectors, below the Government of the State. 
"The performance of the economy of Sinaloa during this year has been really very poor, we need to work hard to recover the ground that we lost this year, in 2012 we must double our effort, it was necessary to align the efforts of all and especially the smooth already synchronized of this new government team, let us hope that next year is much better," he said. 
Economic sluggishness 
Loredo López said that events such as the frosts of the beginning of the year have kept the economy of the state and restricts its performance and growth. 
"The fluxe low economic product of several events, among which the frosts, one of the main effects has been a slow economy that is quickly enough to generate economic dynamism that makes it possible to have an acceptable level flows in the trials, products and services and therefore, at the end of the year we are closing far below expectations that we had," he said. 
Redefining the vocation 
Teodoro Salazar Uriarte, president of the Patronale Confederation of the Mexican Republic of Sinaloa said that you want to channel the state towards productive activities more dynamism. 
"In general terms we have observed that it has worked, we believe that it is necessary to develop a long-term programme that redefined the vocation and the economic direction of the state, because it is important that we are out of place all the potential of the human and material resources of Sinaloa," he said. 
Much to do 
The Chairman of the Coparmex stressed the importance of establishing a vision of future channels better efforts by the Government. 
"In general terms, I would say that the Government has made efforts to give good results in different areas, in terms of economic development there has been some advances, but it is important to develop a long-term programma," he said. 
He pointed out that the current administration has shown advances in the way of public policy. 
"There are elements that allow us to say that the Government is more inclusive, what I can say is that we have worked hard, and the Government is aware of the fact that there is still much to do," he said. 
