Quinteto includes the country in turn to celebrate two decades 
"Go to Costa Rica is a dream that became reality." 
In an exclusive interview with Viva, bassist Jeff Ament, Pearl Jam, said that the group is ready to offer one of its best concerts next Sunday on the National Stadium. 
They have waited more than 20 years, but the group ensures that for them it will be a dream to happen in this country. 
Bassist and founding member Jeff Ament said, speaking exclusively with Viva Brazil last week. 
The group is in the South American side of its tour of celebration of two decades of work and Sunday 20 will make its unique stopover in Central America. 
This day will be available on the National Stadium, from 19:30 hours, alongside the Group of Los Angeles The X and Las Robertas. 
This is an excerpt of the conversation, the full transcript is in La Nación on the Internet. 
For its Costa Rican followers, the fact that Pearl Jam will happen in Costa Rica is a dream: are you aware of what your fans live? 
Go to Costa Rica is a dream that has become reality for us too. 
This is our second time in South America and Central and until now it has been awesome. 
I spent in Costa Rica only once the holidays; it is a country so beautiful and I think we can spend a few days. 
We émotionne our music there. 
I would ask you, because there is a kind of devotion to the group, the fans live in the previous days. 
What is your message to your most ardent supporters? 
Thank you for staying beside us for all these years. 
There have been 21 years for us in Costa Rica; thank you for having waited so long and we are sorry for the fact that so much time has had to spend up to this concert. 
Some people are already saying that the concert is the biggest show of the year. 
Does this adds a bit of pressure on your visit. 
Some of the greatest shows that we have offered during the last 21 years have taken place in the last two weeks. 
We have offered a two huge shows in Sao Paolo and we hope that this has been for this concert in Costa Rica. 
We are very eager to produce. 
We love this country, we love to surf and the jungle; for the two things, Costa Rica is one of the best countries in the world. 
How have you discovered Costa Rica and its waves for surfing? 
We have a lot of surfers friends and I have a very good friend who lives in Tamarindo and the waves are amazing there. 
My friends would always be surfing in Costa Rica and Nicaragua, Mexico, are great places to do; it is that we have learned, through the gents who love surfing. 
Seeing the tour, you offered huge shows, with a lot of songs. 
What have you planned for your presentation to Costa Rica? 
As we have never produced there, we have no restrictions with regard to what we can do. 
We will try to make the best possible show, with a wide variety of songs; we will try to interpret two songs from each album and give our fans a good and diverse repertoire. 
You never repeat the repertoire. 
What is this? 
I believe that this is partly because we have nine discs and we can interpret more than 120 songs and everybody likes different songs, that is why it is very difficult to choose which songs interpret each evening. 
When we have two or three songs in the repertoire that we have seen for a very long time, it helps to stay focused and surprises us because it reminds us why we love these songs and that we can have forgotten. 
The show is more interesting for us and therefore I believe that it is also becoming more interesting for people. 
With this tour, you celebrate 20 years of trajectory. 
Looking back, it is hard to believe everything that you have succeeded? 
Yes, absolutely. 
First, I believe that none of us had imagined that we would form a great rock group, and the fact that we have done for more than 20 years is that it seems a dream. 
We continue to tell our blessings and the fact that we can continue to make music together we émotionne a lot. 
We love and we love to create music. 
We are fortunate to go to places in the world that we have always wanted to go. 
Things could be better for us. 
What does it mean for you to have been a fundamental element in the creation of the grunge? 
It has always been an honour for us to form part of this group of large groups. 
We are very close friends with the people of Soundgarden, Mudhoney and Alice in Chains. 
It is surprising when a movement arises from a group of friends and is not very common. 
From time to time, a group of a city, but it is much more strange when five or ten groups out simultaneously in the same city. 
We are proud, and it is an honour for us to form part of the group in Seattle. 
We still play with some of them from time to time. 
Last year we participated in a festival with Alice in Chains and we have been in Canada with Mudhoney, we have seen Soundgarden in their tour, so we are fortunate to be friends with them and it is an honour for us to form part of the Seattle that has emerged. 
It is also very strange that a group like your stays united and with the same members for so long. 
Yes, four of us have been together for 21 years and Matt (Cameron) joined us 13 years ago, and this is much more time than many groups normally. 
First, I believe that we are all lucky to be alive and, secondly, we are concerned for all the others. 
We are all close friends and that there are musical boulevards that give freedom to everyone to experiment. 
We trust each other with the music of everyone and it could get better. 
Your relationship with the word celebrity has not been easy; however, thanks to your success, you have been able to do what you want. 
How do you find a balance? 
As we grew up, it has been easier for us to find a balance. 
We make sure that we do not spend too much time on tour because it is easy to fall into this game of large masses and people who love your music. 
If you do not forget that people are there for the music, it helps us not forget that we must respect the music and, without putting in mind the fact that it is famous and a rock star, which does not really interested in any of us. 
How do you remember your other project, Mother Love Bone? 
I think we have written good songs and at the beginning it was awesome. 
We have been a group for almost three years and we have not published a disk before the death of Andy (Andrew Woods). 
There has been a lot of frustration for the fact that it lasted so little, and the most important is the fact that we are still very friends with Bruce (Fairweather) and Greg (Gilmore), which started in the group with us and when I hear a song or I see a picture I think of the incredible person that Andy was and how it made me laugh, it was always a pleasure to work, laugh, talk about music, football and many other things with him. 
He was a human being surprising and we lack. 
The national group Las Robertas will open the show in Costa Rica. 
It is true that you know his work, especially Eddie Vedder and for that you have chosen for the opening? 
Yes, we sent videos with different proposals and this one was the group that we liked the most, so we are eager to see what Las Robertas can offer live and it must be very entertaining. 
What you always change the words of Yello Ledbetter live? 
It is a question for Ed (Eddie Vedder), so I don't know. 
It is he who sings and I think that it does so with the first words he imagines. 
Like bassiste, what are its influences? 
There are so many... 
Among the first I remember Geezer Butler, John Entwistle, C. J. Ramone, John Doe, Paul McCartney, Chuck Dukowski... 
There are so many influences, that I could talk all afternoon on the bassistes that I love. 
How has Pearl Jam has maintained the grunge despite the fact that it is no longer fashionable? 
I believe that all of us feel a little disconnected from the word grunge. 
When I think, it reminds me of the groups that I have just mentioned, such as Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all those who have appeared at the same time, and if it is now, I think this is wonderful, because it is a music that is worthwhile to listen and groups like Mudhoney are now music better than ever. 
At the beginning, his music had a more obscure content, and now it has become more positive. 
What should this change? 
It is interesting, because I believe that there are songs in the new album that seem lighter, but there are also songs, such as The End Just Breathe " qualified as very obscure songs, even if they can sound a little positive. 
With the two, when Ed played for me, I cried when I have listened to them and they are deeply obscure songs. 
