Park or mountain? 
The architects coincide on the advisability of convening beyond the controversy about the fees 
The municipal contest on 16 doors opens the debate on the role of Collserola in Barcelona 
In the middle of the 1980s, heyday of the already extinguished Corporation Barcelona Metropolitan (CMB), this Administration has printed posters to promote Collserola. 
The brochure described the mountain as the great park in metropolitan Barcelona. 
In addition, it also contained a comparison figures, with the Central Park in New York. 
With the death of the CMB, in 1987, the park has become, in the imagination of many people, the upper limit of Barcelona, the Catalan capital is the only one that does not focus on the north-south axis, if not high (mountain) - low (sea). 
The qualification of Collserola as a natural park is to the advantage of this idea. 
The reference was no longer Central Park or Yellowstone, with pigs in the role of the Yogi Bear. 
This was the situation until, in September, the mayor convened a mega-competition composed of 16 competitions for all gateways to Collserola. 
A door brings to the idea of park, no doubt. 
It is this, or someone wants to put doors on the field. 
The question is: Collserola: park or mountain? 
The competition, both in terms of its organization as a reflection on the town is a topic of conversation all the architects of Barcelona. 
It is almost a recurring theme that two members of this ancient caste of elected officials speak when they see themselves in an elevator. 
And this is one of the few opinions on which three architects of Barcelona, university professors, are presented. 
Miguel Roldán, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayona: the competition is timely. 
For Roldán, after addressing the littoral front "it is necessary to" discuss "the mountain front" because the rhetoric of Ildefons Cerda, green blocks of houses has not been conducted. 
"It takes from the base that the larger park in Barcelona is the beach. 
Among other things for its accessibility. 
Collserola is more complex, "gave the verdict the architect for which the title of" Collserola "contains a" trap lexicon: "There is no need to think about them" such as access to a park, but the delimitation of certain areas in which we must act. " 
Modol, like Roldán and Bayona with experience in the urban world, describes the proposal as an "intellectual challenge" with "a few perils." 
The perils of "the uncertainty of the projection of public space" after the experience in the 1980s and has been in the area of the Forum, "his swan song." 
The first fear is the demarcation of borders on which we can build. 
"Limiting something means the next step," i.e., its excess. 
"We need to think about new instruments planning, planning, because the current reference to the Metropolitan General Plan (MGP) ] can cause genuine disasters." 
More to the point, Modol felt that, by simplifying the region's El Valles Collserola "can be understood as a park, Barcelona, no." 
Modol recalls that there is already a work done by the Collserola Patronat "must not be lost," thanks for the opportunity that the town hall offers its corporation to intervene in this project "from the first moment." 
In addition, it meant that the proximity of the mountains with the city is the free ticket that allows architects to enter the debate, but "doubt" whether this looming technique must lead multidisciplinary teams ("a success," he says) that: "We, the architects, should only be an instrument." 
Bayona hints that the answer to the question that gives the title of this piece is complex, because of the bases of the competition it lacks a comprehensive vision of Collserola: "We convened 16 cross-cutting competition - he said - in the mountains, but there is not a longitudinal reading and understanding the area as a whole." 
This is, at least in this case, that he has chosen to participate in the 16 contests. 
In another way, a project so that one of the doors can shock in the programme and definition with that of the architect of the gate. 
In his opinion, yes, the town hall should ensure that the band immediately superior to that of Dalt Ronda should include, in all its extension, an area of equipment that makes a smooth transition between the city and the green. 
