"This information supports the hypothesis of a normal functioning cruiser at the time of the impact," he said. 
During the press conference, the owner of the SCT, Pérez Jácome, has listed six important elements in the investigation: 
Visual flight: 
According to the normative aircraft, the flight was carried out according to the rules of the visual flight, which means that the crew must have visibility during the flight and on the ground. 
Weather conditions: 
Reports in the AICM were adequate conditions for take-off, and that the aircraft was proceeding towards the boundary area between TE and the State of Mexico there were layers of cloud cover. 
Selected routes: 
It is likely that " cloud the crew has sought a zone of weaker and more visibility to the valley of Cuernavaca. 
Location of the impact. 
The details of the impact and the last registration of the aircraft on the radar coincide, probably before the impact there is no loss of control or alteration of the flight path. 
Dispersal of the remains of the aircraft in a small area. 
The information available so far allows us to assume that the impact took place on a lateral and the right path. 
The pattern of dispersal of remnants of the aircraft allows us to assume that the helicopter crashed on the ground in terms of structural integrity. 
It has not detected traces of fire or explosion. 
In the location of the disaster there is still no trace in the remains of the aircraft of a type of explosion or fire. 
The latest results of the investigation indicate that the aircraft had multiple contacts with the ground. 
During the field work we found pieces of the aircraft at a height of 9,000,200 feet above the average level of the sea, the soil had a slope that runs from seven dégrées to 30 degrees of inclination. 
The photographs show the sequence in which he was possibly désarticulé during his journey. 
Information provides elements that seem to indicate that the helicopter may have had multiple impactes with the ground. 
After careful research in an area larger than the area circled around the accident, it has not found disperses pieces of the aircraft, which bears the presumption that the impact took place in conditions of integrity. 
MSS announcement protocol to find the gene for obesity 
Social Insurance is leading an investigation to discover the gene for obesity in the case of children and young people; this is borne by experts from the NPI 
The Mexican Institute for Social Insurance (IMSS) has announced that he is leading an investigation to discover the gene for obesity in the case of children and young people, called the protocol " notion of obesity in children and adolescents' which will have the genetic markers associated with overweight. 
In a press release, the head of the Unit of Biochemistry Medical Investigation of Expertise Hospital National Medical Centre of the 20th Century, Miguel Cruz Lopez, explained that it had formed a multidisciplinary team of doctors, nurses, nutritionists and social assistants. 
This team is supported by experts and students from third round of the National Institute of Public Health (INSP) and the Center for Investigation and Advanced Study (Cinvestav) of the National Polytechnic Institute (NPI). 
The investigation is invited to participate or not, to present themselves to the participating sports units of the IMSS Valle de México, where is the evidence for minors every Saturday from 8:00 pm. 
He stressed that the protocol began in the Cuauhtémoc Sports Unit (Estado de México Poniente) and that from October 8, the activity is taking place in the Nezahualcóyolt Sports Unit (Estado de México Oriente). 
Having achieved the goal of bringing together 500 or 600 minors, the study will continue in the Sports Unit Independencia (south of Distrito Federal) and finally in the Morelos Sports Unit (north of Distrito Federal). 
He explained that the purpose of this investigation and know the components and the importance of genetics in relation to the development of obesity and to identify among children and young Mexican risk factors to prevent the onset of chronic degenerative diseases. 
As we celebrate on 14 November the World Day of the Diabètes, he mentioned that the aim is to bring together three thousand children and young people between six and 14 years, with the consent and under the supervision of their parents, for the application of specific questionnaires to food. 
They will also be asked about their physical activity and their family history of heredity diseases, to avoid the risk factors that trigger diseases such as diabetes or kidney failure. 
He detailed that Saturday will be applied to all participants of the anthropometric measurements (weight, height, waist circumference, blood pressure, determination of the levels of glucose, triglycerides, cholesterol and insulin and seeks to identify the people associated with childhood obesity). 
López Cruz pointed out that this investigation is the result of the concern of health professionals for the alarming weight in the case of minors. 
"The health surveys of 1999 and 2006 reported that in just six years there has been an increase in the case of boys, 77% in obesity and in the case of girls 47 percent; as far as overweight has also increased dramatique', said the IMSS specialist. 
He said that the justification for the search for the markers is based on the fact that the population of the country is different from the others by its genetic history. 
He was informed that on average, the Mexican has a 65% of Indian-American ancestry, a 30% and a five percent African and this condition is reflected in the people associated with diabetes and overweight. 
He explained that in general, the genetics of obesity is reflected in the inability of burning the excess energy that it consumes (calories), which is deposited in the form of fat. 
The researcher explained that the direct benefit for participants is the full evaluation of children, which makes it possible to detect if they are overweight or obese. 
However, he said that the presence of dark folds (acanthosis) on the neck and arm indicate the likelihood of suffering metabolic alterations and even pre-diabetes. 
Information is managed in a confidential manner, doctors put in writing to the parents, which explains each of the measures and changes in the lifestyle that they must do to prevent disease. 
López Cruz explained that there are three main components that cause overweight, obesity and other chronic ailments: sedentary lifestyles, which is the lack of physical activity daily, stay most of the day sitting in front of the TV and use means of transport instead of walking short distances. 
Another reason is the high intake, i.e. the largest consumption of sweet drinks, carbohydrate (tamales - pâté of meat cornmeal wrapped in leaves of corn, bread, pizza, hamburgers, etc.) with a high content of fats and proteins and genetic analysis in this protocol. 
Asphalt UNAM blackcurrants 
Rafael Herrera, a researcher at the Faculty of Chemistry of UNAM, develops asphaltes modified with polymers to produce a mixture with a better performance, regardless of environmental conditions and temperature 
If the signales that the streets were resolved, it would no longer be necessary to repair around 200 thousand blackcurrants every season of rain in the Metropolitan Area of Valle de México, warned Rafael Herrera Nájera, a researcher at the Faculty of Chemistry (FQ-resistant gonorrhea) of the UNAM, which has ensured that if the process of construction and maintenance of bituminous pavement is adequate, blackcurrants could be reduced or even eliminated. 
During its conference A technological opinion on blackcurrants, organised in the framework of the International Year of Chemistry, he announced that the laboratory which he is responsible for developing asphaltes modified with polymers to produce a mixture with characteristics similar to those of asphalt, but with greater mechanical resistance, both high and low temperatures. 
Nájera Herrera has estimated that this type of modified asphaltes could be used in places where the climate is extremely hot, as some cities in the north of the country, to improve performance, and consequently, the training of blackcurrants. 
He explained that the asphalt, the heaviest share of oil, is a set of molecules of hydrocarbons, molecules with a molecular weight heavier, called asphaltenes and molecules with a molecular weight, called malthènes, which together give paved its characteristic viscoelastic behaviour. 
The viscoelastic behaviour of asphalt is the fact that at high temperatures, nearly 180 degrees, behaves like a liquid, 120 degrees Celsius its viscosity is very high and 50 degrees Celsius it presents an almost solid state, while at very low temperatures, asphalt becomes brittle, he added. 
This means that in the streets the resistance of the asphalt is not uniform and changed during the day depending on environmental conditions and temperatures, warns the specialist in chemical engineering. 
The FQ-resistant gonorrhea researcher observed that the streets of Ciudad de México in their majority were covered by a flexible pavement, composed of six layers of materials, including the last three involve asphalt. 
Among the most superficial layers is the layer of asphalt, formed by small stones drenched in asphalt and compacted later. 
Each of the small stones that form the layer, signalât says, is asphalt. 
When the vehicles are generating efforts, it allows that the forces spread very well in the streets. 
If we had modified asphalt, they are transmitted better, opinât the chemical engineers. 
On the asphalt layer, he said, a final layer called turnover layer gemstone, i.e., sand, which is also bathed in asphalt. 
As it is in contact with the wheels of vehicles, it must have more mechanical strength than the asphalt layer and provide grip on the street. 
As part of the pavement that receives and distributes the effort, the layer of rotation also requires that it has an adequate thickness and the material it is made must be treated. 
The weather, especially humidity and temperature variations, are also a very important factor to consider, especially water, he said, because they affect significantly the performance of the asphalt layer. 
When the soil is wet, water spreads inside the layer is difficult, which softened all layers of the pavement and therefore cassis. 
In the trial of a cassis, he said, the first blight is the film rolling and only later affected the asphalt layer, but the damage does not take place immediately, but it is a process that must be treated to the first signals with proper maintenance programs. 
The member of the National System Researchers explained that the burden of vehicles is another important factor for the formation of cassis and therefore the thickness of each layer must be always linked to the burden of vehicles and ensure its satisfaction, to avoid the frequent formation of blackcurrants. 
Rafael Herrera warned that there is still much to investigate and work on the asphalt, for example, the bitumineuses emulsions, which in other countries already exist on the market and make it possible to repair the blackcurrants easily and without having to use high temperatures. 
