Rates are rising, the stock markets flanchent 
The risk of contagion from the debt crisis still undermines European indices. 
Despite the appointment of new heads of government in Greece and Italy and better growth figures in France and Germany, the rates of vulnerable countries continue their ascent. 
Always worried about the stability of the eurozone, the European stock markets moved a little more into negative territory, Tuesday 15 November. 
